cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper proposes a new normalization technique for deep neural networks that is applicable to various network architectures and tasks, and is robust to a wide range of batch sizes. The paper also presents analyses of the proposed technique. Given these characteristics, the most likely sub-category is computer vision (cs.CV), followed by machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and multimedia (cs.MM).
